column2: > In this experiment, you will be asked to make judgments about the content of different sentences.
> On each trial, you will read a sentence, and will be shown a picture immediately following the sentence.
> Your task is to decide whether the object displayed in the picture was mentioned in the sentence or not
> and respond as quickly as possible by pressing S for yes or N for no.
> You will now do a practice session with feedback and instructions.
> Click the button below to continue.

column2: > You are about to begin the practice test.
> On each trial, a sentence will appear on the screen. You should press SPACEBAR when you have read and understood the sentence.
> After you press SPACEBAR, a picture will appear on the screen.
> You need to indicate whether or not the pictured object was mentioned in the sentence.
> If the object WAS mentioned in the preceding sentence, you should press S
> If the object was NOT mentioned in the preceding sentence, you should press N.
> Click the button below to continue to the practice session.
